CM_ BO_ 1039  "Die Nachricht korrespondiert mit der Nachricht \"GPS Uhrzeit MOST\".
Je nach Verbauvariante des Fahrzeuges werden die Navi-Daten vom MOST in den CAN (Fahrzeug mit Navigation, Signalnamen enth�lt MOST) oder vom CAN in den MOST (Fahrzeug ohne Navigation, Signalnamen enth�lt CAN) gesendet.
Nachricht wird beim Aufstarten, bei erster g�ltiger Signalverf�gbarkeit und anschlie�end bei jedem Wechsel bei den Minuten gesendet (sobald die Sekunde den Wert 00 durchlaufen hat).
Ab ATM2: Die Botschaft enth�lt die Schaltsekunden.
The message corresponds with the message \"GPS Uhrzeit MOST\".
Depending on vehicle option variants, the positioning data is either sent from MOST to CAN (vehicles with navigation, Signal name includes MOST), or from CAN to MOST (vehicles with Telematics but no navigation, Signal name includes CAN).
==========
The message corresponds to the message \"GPS Uhrzeit MOST\".
Depending on the installation variant of the vehicle, the navigation data are sent from the MOST to the CAN (vehicle with navigation system, signal name contains \"MOST\") or from the CAN to the MOST (vehicle without navigation system, signal name contains CAN).
Message is sent during start-up upon first valid signal availability and subsequently upon each minute change (as soon as the second has passed the value 00).
From ATM2: The message contains the switching seconds.
The message corresponds to the message \"GPS Uhrzeit MOST\".
Depending on vehicle option variants, the positioning data is either sent from MOST to CAN (vehicles with navigation, Signal name includes MOST), or from CAN to MOST (vehicles with Telematics but no navigation, Signal name includes CAN).";
